		<description>Good point and thank you for comment.

I would argue that this is true only if value you gain from that marketing is greater than value you lose from people who left, but otherwise wouldn&#039;t.

What Facebook Connect is for visitors is trust by proxy. I might not trust you enough, but I do Facebook to enter. Hence strong brands have less to gain from it than weaker.

I guess at the end, like with so many other things, it depends on particular case (website).</description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Good point and thank you for comment.</p>
<p>I would argue that this is true only if value you gain from that marketing is greater than value you lose from people who left, but otherwise wouldn&#8217;t.</p>
<p>What Facebook Connect is for visitors is trust by proxy. I might not trust you enough, but I do Facebook to enter. Hence strong brands have less to gain from it than weaker.</p>
<p>I guess at the end, like with so many other things, it depends on particular case (website).</p>
